inputs.title: CFG Cheat Sheet (important and often tuned wrong)
inputs.note:
CFG (Classifier-Free Guidance) Cheat Sheet

This controls how strongly the prompt influences each frame.

LOW sample CFG:
start = 2.0
range = 1.5 – 3.0

HIGH sample CFG:
start = 4.5
range = 3.5 – 6.0


What LOW CFG does:
Stabilizes identity and prevents prompt from changing the face.

If LOW CFG too high:
- face reshapes
- age changes
- makeup changes

If LOW CFG too low:
- soft face
- weak detail


What HIGH CFG does:
Controls how strongly motion and prompt details appear.

If HIGH CFG too high:
- flicker
- new clothing
- new person
- over-sharpening

If HIGH CFG too low:
- dull motion
- weak expression
- washed out frames


Simple rule:
LOW CFG keeps the person.
HIGH CFG drives the performance.


Safe starting pair:
low cfg = 2.0
high cfg = 4.5

inputs.title: shift and boundary cheat sheet
inputs.note:
Quick cheat-sheet one-liner version

Default combo — High shift 7.0 / Low shift 4.2 / Boundary 0.75
New person walking in strong → High shift ↑ to 7.5–8.0, boundary ↓ to 0.70–0.72
Existing person locked tight → High shift ↓ to 6.0–6.5, boundary ↑ to 0.82–0.88
End too noisy → Low shift ↓ to 3.8–4.0
End too soft → Low shift ↑ to 4.8–5.2
